7 FIRST REGULAR SESSION
8 HOUSE AMENDMENT “ ” to COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “A” to H.P. 131,
9 L.D. 209, “An Act to Make Supplemental Appropriations and Allocations from the General
10 Fund and Other Funds for the Expenditures of State Government and to Change Certain
11 Provisions of the Law Necessary to the Proper Operations of State Government for the
12 Fiscal Year Ending June 30, 2025”
13 Amend the amendment by inserting after Part X the following:
14 'PART Y
15 Sec. Y-1. State employees required to pay premiums for paid family and
16 medical leave. Notwithstanding any provision of the Maine Revised Statutes, Title 26,
17 chapter 7, subchapter 6-C to the contrary, an employee of State Government, including an
18 employee in the executive, legislative or judicial branch and a state department or agency,
19 is responsible for paying the employee's share of the premium imposed pursuant to Title
20 26, section 850-F, subsection 3 until the State receives approval for a private plan pursuant
21 to Title 26, section 850-H and the State is no longer required to pay the premium.'
22 Amend the amendment by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
23 section number to read consecutively.
24 SUMMARY
2255 This amendment requires an employee of State Government, including an employee in
2266 the executive, legislative or judicial branch and a state department or agency, to pay that
2277 employee's share of the premium imposed under the paid family and medical leave law
2288 until the State receives approval for a private plan and is no longer required to pay the
2299 premium.
